channel.title: Java crap
channel.description:
Java crap.... Ok, I was running a gameserver on my pc (Java), but when I got a java update, the servers suddenly stopped working.... Any help? I'm using Winux Vista/2007.09 64-Bit* So any help?
*Ubuntu 7.04

item.title: Java crap
item.dc:creator: @moparisthebest Moparisthebest
item.description:
@moparisthebest wrote:

You have compiled with a higher version than your jre.

sudo apt-get install sun-java6-jdk sun-java6-jre

will fix your problem

item.dc:creator: @The_Un-Named The Un-Named
item.description:
@The_Un-Named wrote:

As far as I know, Java 1.5 becomes the default command line jdk, this includes javac, so your compiling into Java 1.5, witch isn’t supported by 1.4 or earlier versions, I know you fixed your error but it’s nice to know what went wrong.

Linky.
